examples.en: Her success stems from hard work.
Dependence on alcohol often stems from unhappiness in the home.
Stems bearing slender wands of flowers
Always cut stems obliquely to enable flowers to absorb more water.
The red stems of this bush provide a contrast to the drab brown of the winter garden.
With its spreading stems, ivy makes good ground cover.
The increase in the national debt stems from the last war.
The rattan's stems are split into willowy staves that are woven together to produce exquisite baskets.
If you anatomize the problem, you'll see it stems from a combination of her bad behavior and your unwillingness to speak to her about it.
